result.execSummary:
The defendant Daniel Lee Will Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

11:48 am cases called. 14CF27 & 14CF40. Defendant Daniel Lee Will in court with attorney Bryan D. Keberlein.  Steven P. Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. ADA Anderson recites recommendation on record. State moves to amend 14CF27 to Misd. OMWOC-Abandon within 24 hours-943.23(3m) and amend 14CF40 to Misd. Bail Jumping-946.49(1)(a).   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Court accepts motion of State to amend charges. Plea: No Contest to 14CF27 & 14CF40. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in 14TR339 & 14TR440. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Keberlein. Statement by defendant. Statement by Court prior to sentencing. Court sentences the defendant to-each case: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years. CONDITIONS on 14CF27 ONLY: 20 days WCJ, with Huber. Court does not object to jail transfer. To begin no later than October 1, 2014.  CONDITIONS on BOTH: AODA and follow through, Absolute sobriety, No Bars, no ingestion of any imparing substance unless with a valid prescription from a physician. Restitution in the amount of $1,436.24. to be paid in increments of no less than $100 per month commencing October 1, 2014. Terms of Agent. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Appeal Rights Given.
